{
  "title": "Clock",
  "description": "High-precision wall-clock that accumulates elapsed time while running. Reads from performance.now via `getPreciseTime`. Use Clock.start, Clock.stop, Clock.reset, and Clock.restart to control the running state; read elapsed time via Clock.elapsedTime (the Time instance is shared — copy it if you need to keep a snapshot). Use Timer for a clock with a fixed limit and `expired` flag.",
